Installation
============

$ ./install

On Mac:
  - If using iterm2 make sure to change preferences > profiles > Terminal > Report Terminal Type to "xterm-256color"

If .gitconfig is not applying the global .gitignore, use the command:
  $ git config --global core.excludesfile ~/.gitignore

Exuberant ctags must be installed for vim autocomplete features:
On mac:
$ brew install ctags-exuberant

Then to generated the ctags, navigate to the project directory and run:
$ ctags -R .

You can then jump to a definition with <c-]>

Make sure to install vim plugins:
$ vim ~/.vimrc
:PlugInstall

On linux if .bash_profile isn't being sourced, add to .bashrc:
source ~/.bash_profile
